cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.NE 

This paper deals with visual recognition and context reasoning, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of human psychophysics experiments and mouse clicks to identify clicking patterns and features suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed model also involves recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
